en_189748_0	A group of United National Party backbenchers are getting ready to make a written request today (May 02) to Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe requesting a meeting with him.
en_189748_1	They want to further discuss the party restructuring process.
en_189748_2	The UNP backbenchers had arrived at this decision after having a discussion at the Parliamentary Complex yesterday.
en_189748_3	A letter signed by 16 UNP MP’s would be handed over to the PM’s Office today.
en_189748_4	It was reported that another discussion was held yesterday between UNP MPs and Ministers at Temple Trees.
en_189748_5	The future course of action within the party had been discussed there.
en_189748_6	However, several backbenchers had not participated in this meeting.
